      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        " Load Pre-trained PEGASUS Model and Tokenizer\n",
        "What this does:\n",
        "This step loads a pre-trained PEGASUS model and its tokenizer. We'll use google/pegasus-cnn_dailymail, which was fine-tuned on the CNN/DailyMail news summarization dataset after being pre-trained with the GSG objective.\n",
        "Why it's necessary:\n",
        "The tokenizer converts text into tokens (subword units) that the model can process. The model itself contains the encoder-decoder architecture with pre-trained weights. Loading these to GPU memory prepares them for inference."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Es1yyrrN5h0y"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "model_name = \"google/pegasus-cnn_dailymail\"\n",
        "\n",
        "tokenizer = PegasusTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_name)\n",
        "model = PegasusForConditionalGeneration.from_pretrained(model_name)\n",
        "\n",
        "device = \"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\"\n",
        "model.to(device)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"device:\", device)\n",
        "print(\"params:\", f\"{model.num_parameters():,}\")"
      ],
