    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Step 4: Create a Simple Summarization Function\n",
        "What this does:\n",
        "This step creates a reusable function that takes any text input and generates a summary using the PEGASUS model. It handles tokenization, inference, and decoding back to human-readable text.\n",
        "Why it's necessary:\n",
        "This encapsulates the complete summarization pipeline: tokenize → encode → decode → generate summary. This is the core inference process described in the PEGASUS paper."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "J0KG_b4g_xXO"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def generate_summary(text, max_length=128, min_length=32, num_beams=4, length_penalty=2.0):\n",
        "    inputs = tokenizer(\n",
        "        text,\n",
        "        max_length=512,\n",
        "        truncation=True,\n",
        "        padding=\"max_length\",\n",
        "        return_tensors=\"pt\"\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    inputs = {k: v.to(device) for k, v in inputs.items()}\n",
        "\n",
        "    summary_ids = model.generate(\n",
        "        inputs[\"input_ids\"],\n",
        "        attention_mask=inputs[\"attention_mask\"],\n",
        "        max_length=max_length,\n",
        "        min_length=min_length,\n",
        "        num_beams=num_beams,\n",
        "        length_penalty=length_penalty,\n",
        "        early_stopping=True\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    return tokenizer.decode(summary_ids[0], skip_special_tokens=True)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "vhZFKDeg_yxB"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Step 5: Test Summarization on Sample Text\n",
        "What this does:\n",
        "This step tests our summarization pipeline on a sample news article. We'll see PEGASUS in action, demonstrating how the pre-trained model (trained with Gap Sentence Generation) performs abstractive summarization.\n",
        "Why it's necessary:\n",
        "This validates that our pipeline works end-to-end and lets you see the quality of PEGASUS summaries. Since this model was fine-tuned on CNN/DailyMail, it performs especially well on news articles."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "F-dfYLjaARZ_"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "text = \"\"\"\n",
        "The historic launch of NASA's James Webb Space Telescope represents a major milestone\n",
        "in astronomical research. After decades of development and numerous delays, the telescope\n",
        "finally launched on December 25, 2021, aboard an Ariane 5 rocket from French Guiana.\n",
        "The telescope is designed to observe the universe in infrared wavelengths, allowing it\n",
        "to peer through cosmic dust and see farther back in time than ever before. Scientists\n",
        "expect it to revolutionize our understanding of the early universe, star formation,\n",
        "and potentially detect signs of life on distant exoplanets. The telescope's primary\n",
        "mirror spans 6.5 meters in diameter, nearly three times larger than Hubble's mirror,\n",
        "giving it significantly more light-gathering capability. It orbits at a point called\n",
        "L2, about 1.5 million kilometers from Earth, where it can maintain a stable temperature\n",
        "critical for infrared observations. The mission cost approximately $10 billion and\n",
        "involved contributions from NASA, the European Space Agency, and the Canadian Space Agency.\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "summary = generate_summary(text)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"TEXT:\\n\", text.strip())\n",
        "print(\"\\n---\\nSUMMARY:\\n\", summary)\n",
        "print(f\"\\n---\\nWords: {len(text.split())} -> {len(summary.split())}\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "4jqz0TRw_9qt",
        "outputId": "571b7e50-b6b3-47bb-a11a-ccd496114fb4"
      },
