        "Step 9: Batch Summarization (Multiple Texts)What this does:\n",
        "Process multiple documents at once using batch processing. This is much more efficient than processing one-by-one, especially with GPU acceleration.Why it's necessary:\n",
        "In real applications, you often need to summarize many documents. Batching leverages GPU parallelism for significant speedups."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "n9H2plAME9fH"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import time\n",
        "\n",
        "def batch_summarize(texts, max_length=64, min_length=10, batch_size=4):\n",
        "    summaries = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i in range(0, len(texts), batch_size):\n",
        "        batch = texts[i:i + batch_size]\n",
        "\n",
        "        inputs = tokenizer(\n",
        "            batch,\n",
        "            max_length=512,\n",
        "            truncation=True,\n",
        "            padding=True,\n",
        "            return_tensors=\"pt\"\n",
        "        ).to(device)\n",
        "\n",
        "        with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "            summary_ids = model.generate(\n",
        "                inputs[\"input_ids\"],\n",
        "                attention_mask=inputs[\"attention_mask\"],\n",
        "                max_length=max_length,\n",
        "                min_length=min_length,\n",
        "                num_beams=4,\n",
        "                length_penalty=2.0,\n",
        "                early_stopping=True,\n",
        "                no_repeat_ngram_size=3\n",
        "            )\n",
        "\n",
        "        summaries.extend([\n",
        "            tokenizer.decode(ids, skip_special_tokens=True)\n",
        "            for ids in summary_ids\n",
        "        ])\n",
        "\n",
        "    return summaries\n",
        "\n",
        "articles = [\n",
        "    \"Electric vehicles are becoming increasingly popular as governments worldwide push for reduced carbon emissions. Tesla leads the market, but traditional automakers like Ford and GM are catching up with new EV models.\",\n",
        "    \"Artificial intelligence is transforming healthcare through improved diagnostics and personalized treatment plans. Machine learning algorithms can now detect diseases from medical images with accuracy matching or exceeding human doctors.\",\n",
        "    \"The global semiconductor shortage has disrupted manufacturing across industries. Car makers and electronics companies face production delays as chip demand outstrips supply, leading to price increases and longer wait times.\",\n",
        "    \"Remote work has become permanent for many companies following the pandemic. Studies show productivity has remained stable while employees report better work-life balance, though some miss in-person collaboration.\",\n",
        "    \"Cryptocurrency markets experienced extreme volatility with Bitcoin reaching new highs before sharp corrections. Regulatory uncertainty and institutional adoption debates continue to drive price swings in digital assets.\"\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "start = time.time()\n",
        "summaries = batch_summarize(articles, batch_size=2)\n",
        "elapsed = time.time() - start\n",
        "\n",
        "for article, summary in zip(articles, summaries):\n",
        "    print(\"In: \", article[:80], \"...\")\n",
        "    print(\"Out:\", summary, \"\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Total time: {elapsed:.2f}s | Avg: {elapsed/len(articles):.2f}s/article\")"
