        "Step 10: Understanding PEGASUS Pre-training (Gap Sentence Generation)\n",
        "What this does:\n",
        "This step demonstrates the core concept from the PEGASUS paper: Gap Sentence Generation (GSG). We'll simulate how PEGASUS was pre-trained by masking important sentences and having the model predict them.\n",
        "Why it's necessary:\n",
        "Understanding GSG helps you appreciate why PEGASUS excels at summarization. The pre-training objective directly teaches the model to identify and generate important sentences - exactly what summarization requires."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jjGCdY9xhbcf"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import random\n",
        "\n",
        "demo_text = \"\"\"\n",
        "The Amazon rainforest plays a crucial role in regulating Earth's climate.\n",
        "It absorbs billions of tons of carbon dioxide each year.\n",
        "Deforestation rates have increased dramatically in recent years.\n",
        "Scientists warn this could trigger irreversible climate tipping points.\n",
        "The forest is home to millions of species.\n",
        "Indigenous communities have lived there for thousands of years.\n",
        "International efforts aim to protect remaining forest areas.\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "sentences = [s.strip() + '.' for s in demo_text.split('.') if s.strip()]\n",
        "gaps = random.sample(range(len(sentences)), 2)\n",
        "\n",
        "masked = \" \".join([\"[MASK]\" if i in gaps else s for i, s in enumerate(sentences)])\n",
        "target = \" \".join([sentences[i] for i in sorted(gaps)])\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"In: \", masked)\n",
        "print(\"Out:\", target)"
      ],
