        "Step 16: Implementing PEGASUS + LoRA (PEFT)\n",
        "What this does:\n",
        "We'll use LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation) to fine-tune PEGASUS efficiently. LoRA only trains a tiny fraction of parameters (~0.1-1%), preventing overfitting on small datasets.\n",
        "Why LoRA is ideal:\n",
        "\n",
        "Prevents overfitting - freezes original weights, adds small trainable adapters\n",
        "Memory efficient - trains <1% of parameters\n",
        "Better for small datasets - exactly your situation\n",
        "Easy to merge/swap - can load/unload LoRA weights"
      ],
