    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Experiment Conclusion: Full Fine-Tuning vs. LoRA on PEGASUS\n",
        "\n",
        "After observing severe model degradation and confident hallucinations (\"Samsung Galaxy S8 Edge\", \"Transformer Book 2\") during standard full-parameter fine-tuning, we pivoted to Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning (PEFT) using Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA).\n",
        "\n",
        "By targeting only the attention heads (`q_proj` and `v_proj`) of the `pegasus-xsum` model, we achieved the following optimizations:\n",
        "\n",
        "### Empirical Comparison\n",
        "| Metric | Full Fine-Tuning | LoRA Fine-Tuning | Reduction / Improvement |\n",
        "| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n",
        "| **Trainable Parameters** | 767,616,000 (100%) | 1,572,864 (0.20%) | **99.8% Reduction** |\n",
        "| **Training Time (5 Epochs)** | ~260 seconds | ~9.5 seconds | **27x Faster** |\n",
        "| **Final Training Loss** | 3.77 | 3.45 | **Improved Convergence** |\n",
        "\n",
        "### Key Findings\n",
        "1. **Catastrophic Forgetting Prevented:** Freezing the 568M base parameters preserved the model's foundational linguistic capabilities, preventing the \"word salad\" and archaic hardware hallucinations seen in Phase 1.\n",
        "2. **Resource Efficiency:** LoRA proved that updating merely 0.20% of the transformer's weights is sufficient to steer the generation style, heavily reducing VRAM requirements and allowing for consumer-grade GPU training."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Gcx70FPIGsnE"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import evaluate\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load ROUGE metric\n",
        "rouge = evaluate.load(\"rouge\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Helper function for batch summarization with LoRA model\n",
        "def lora_batch_summarize(texts, max_length=64, batch_size=2):\n",
        "    summaries = []\n",
        "    for i in range(0, len(texts), batch_size):\n",
        "        batch = texts[i:i + batch_size]\n",
        "        inputs = tokenizer(\n",
        "            batch,\n",
        "            max_length=512,\n",
        "            truncation=True,\n",
        "            padding=True,\n",
        "            return_tensors=\"pt\"\n",
        "        ).to(device)\n",
        "\n",
        "        with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "            summary_ids = lora_model.generate(\n",
        "                input_ids=inputs[\"input_ids\"],           # <--- FIXED: Added 'input_ids='\n",
        "                attention_mask=inputs[\"attention_mask\"],\n",
        "                max_length=max_length,\n",
        "                min_length=10,\n",
        "                num_beams=4,\n",
        "                length_penalty=2.0,\n",
        "                early_stopping=True,\n",
        "                no_repeat_ngram_size=3\n",
        "            )\n",
        "\n",
        "        batch_summaries = [\n",
        "            tokenizer.decode(ids, skip_special_tokens=True)\n",
        "            for ids in summary_ids\n",
        "        ]\n",
        "        summaries.extend(batch_summaries)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return summaries\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"=\"*70)\n",
        "print(\"EVALUATING LoRA MODEL\")\n",
        "print(\"=\"*70)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate predictions\n",
        "lora_model.eval()\n",
        "predictions = lora_batch_summarize(train_documents, batch_size=2)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate ROUGE scores\n",
        "results = rouge.compute(predictions=predictions, references=train_summaries)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nROUGE Scores:\")\n",
        "print(\"-\"*70)\n",
        "for key, value in results.items():\n",
        "    print(f\"{key:12s}: {value:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*70)\n",
        "print(\"PREDICTION EXAMPLES\")\n",
        "print(\"=\"*70)\n",
        "\n",
        "for i in range(len(train_documents)):\n",
        "    print(f\"\\nExample {i+1}:\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Input:     {train_documents[i][:80]}...\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Target:    {train_summaries[i]}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Predicted: {predictions[i]}\")\n",
        "    print(\"-\"*70)"
